msContents.summary: Dictionary of the Arabic language originally compiled between 1368 and 1392 whose title translates into English as The ocean. Words are indexed by their last root letter and have brief definitions. Frequent marginal notes.

supportDesc.extent: 480 leaves : 232 x 160 (172 x 112) mm. bound to 235 x 178 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 33-34 long lines; text block framed in ink.

decoDesc.decoNote: Fully illuminated title page (f. 1r) and chapter headings in gold ink with illuminated panels and floral ornaments in a western Persian style of the late 14th or early 15th century; significant words in red, blue, or gold ink; narrow gold border framing text on each page.

binding.p: Early morocco, gilt-stamped center medallion and cornerpieces; leather with gilt and colored ornamentation inside covers.

history.provenance: Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London), cat. 22 (July 2000), no. 63, to Lawrence J. Schoenberg.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
